thread.title: RUMOURS: Arsenal yet to hold extension talks with Wilshere
thread.title_full: RUMOURS: Arsenal yet to hold extension talks with Wilshere

title: RUMOURS: Arsenal yet to hold extension talks with Wilshere
text:
0 Jan 12, 2017 8:02:26 PM The England international is currently taking in a season-long loan spell at Bournemouth and has only 18 months left to run on his Gunners deal 
Arsenal are yet to discuss a contract extension with Jack Wilshere, according to the Daily Star . 
The England international is currently tied to the Gunners until the summer of 2018, but is taking in a season-long loan spell with Bournemouth at present. 
He has proved his form and fitness with the Cherries, leading Arsene Wenger to suggest that fresh terms will be tabled at the Emirates. 
A lack of movement is said to have forced Wilshere to consider his options, though, with the talented midfielder having already sparked reports of interest from Everton and Manchester City.
